HEADWORD: Inconsideration
<hw>In`con*sid`er*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inconsideratio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>inconsid⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety> <def>Lack of due
consideration; inattention to consequences; inconsiderateness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Blindness of mind, <qex>inconsideration</qex>, precipitation.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not gross, willful, deliberate, crimes; but rather the effects of
<qex>inconsideration</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sharp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inconsistence</ent>⟦br⟧
